cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper discusses the fundamental limits of sensor networks for detection problems, which involves communication and information theory concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with system modeling and control, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of sensor networks for detection and classification of targets suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the problem of sensor selection, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the use of chemical sensor arrays, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
